# Festag — no lead under page titles

Do **not** render a second text line under a page `h1` (subtitle, lead, description, eyebrow).

Bad:
- `h1` „Dokumente“ + `p` „Rechnungssteller für Angebote, Rechnungen und Verträge.“
- `.set-page-lead`, `.festag-page-lead`, `.page-lead`, `.dec-m-lead` under the main title
- Duplicating context that belongs in the body or in a section row inside the content card

Prefer:
- **One `h1` only** — put necessary context in the title itself (short, one sentence max) or in the first section inside the content container (`.set-label-sub`, section copy in rows)
- Settings: `SettingsMobileShell` shows title + breadcrumb only — no `SECTION_LEAD` under the header
- Portal/mobile list chrome: large left title without a muted lead under it unless the product spec explicitly requires it for that route

When touching pages that still mount lead lines under `h1`, remove them — do not reintroduce `set-page-lead` or equivalent patterns.
